    <h3> This is a game about the USSR in the future!!!! <br></h3>
   <h4> The action of Atomic Heart takes place in an alternative USSR, in which the country has entered the mass production of robots serving the country's population. The main character of the game is Major Sergei Nechaev, a Soviet intelligence agent under the pseudonym P-3, who arrived at a robot production company codenamed "3826", located in the KazSSR. For an unknown reason, the robots at the facility went haywire and attacked the staff, then took over 3826. Now Major Nechaev will not only have to resolve the situation and stop the robots, but also find out the cause of what happened. The game includes first-person combat; During the game, the character can find and construct a variety of weapons. According to Mundfish CEO Robert Bagratuni, the game world is "the entire Soviet Union, a wide circle" from the Arctic in the north to the Altai Mountains in the south; the game's locations, such as the "3826" underground and above-ground facilities, are scattered across the map and linked by railroads. The development of Atomic Heart was fraught with difficulties: studio staff complained about working conditions, the release date was repeatedly postponed, and some international publications called for a boycott of the game against the background of the Russian invasion of Ukraine due to the possible connection of Mundfish leaders with the Russian authorities. However, after its release, the project received generally positive reviews from both Russian and foreign gaming press. The advantages of Atomic Heart were considered to be a well-developed setting in the Soviet aesthetics, character and environment design, musical accompaniment with original compositions by Mick Gordon and remixes of Soviet pop classics, as well as optimization of the Windows version of the game. The gameplay and story were ambiguously perceived, and the presence of bugs and software failures was criticized. Journalists noted that in many ways the inspiration for the creators of the project was the games of the BioShock and Fallout series.<br></h4>
